<HEADLINE>
LONGHORNS HAVE MOVED ON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE JONES 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Texas guard Will Clay says that if Monday's
practice was any indication, the Longhorns have gone onward through
the lackadaisical fog they appeared to play in during the loss to
Oklahoma in the Big 12 tournament.
</P>
<P>
   ``A great day of practice,'' Clay said. ``Very intense. And
we're going to work hard to get better right up until we play again
Thursday.''
</P>
<P>
   The fifth-seeded Longhorns traveled to Salt Lake City yesterday,
where they open NCAA Tournament play tomorrow in the West Region
against 12th-seeded Indiana State. Declarations of rededication
abound. And if his team learned something of a lesson from the
dismal performance against the Sooners four days ago, so be it,
coach Rick Barnes said. But he also said he could think of better
learning tools.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not a guy who likes to lose games to teach lessons,''
Barnes said. ``Maybe if we play well \Rin the NCAAs\S, I'll look
back and say it was helpful. You lose, you put it behind you, pick
yourself up and go again. I guess you can spin it any way you want
to spin it.''
</P>
<P>
   Center Chris Mihm said the Longhorns should benefit from the Big
12 regular-season war.
</P>
<P>
   ``The conference was fantastic, a dogfight all year,'' Mihm
said. ``There hasn't been an easy game. We had to stay on our toes
to finish 13-3, and it's been difficult. I think that will help
prepare us for the NCAAs.
</P>
<P>
   ``I do think it's going to be refreshing to play some other
teams and see what we can do. It does get a little tedious at times
during conference play when everybody knows what to expect. That's
what makes it special in the NCAA Tournament because you never know
who you're going to play.''
</P>
<P>
   Texas did travel to Utah with one injury concern. Backup point
guard Chris McColpin, who has given the Longhorns some valuable
spot minutes and has tournament experience, sprained an ankle in
Monday's practice. X-rays taken yesterday were negative, but he is
listed as questionable for tomorrow's game.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
