<P>
   CAMPUS-DRINKING (Undated) _ Despite a decade of prevention
efforts, heavy drinking on college campuses continued apace
throughout the 1990s, according to a study by the Harvard School of
Public Health. Attitudes toward alcohol appear to have become more
polarized, with increases in both the number of abstainers, and of
frequent binge drinkers. By Jodi Wigoren.
