<P>
   NY-HUNTS-POINT (New York) _ The Hunts Point Terminal Market, the
giant wholesale produce market in the South Bronx, is the
waystation for the bulk of the fresh vegetables and fruits offered
in the city's restaurants and greengrocers _ the palest endive,
wrapped in tissue, the most tender baby artichokes and clusters of
moist green peanuts, still perfumed with the rich earth they left
in the Everglades the night before. And it is not just the domain
of professional buyers. Although the public is officially
discouraged from shopping there, persistent souls are tolerated if
they come prepared, and the thrill of a bargain there is enhanced
by the awe of being at a crossroads of world commerce, like Times
Square or the floor of the New York Stock Exchange. By Matt Lee and
Ted Lee.
