r e BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE16     03-15 0257
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    WRESTLING GRAPEVINE
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   From his official Web site, Chris Jericho said this about Hulk
Hogan: ``I think the time has come for Hulk Hogan to step down. His
promo on `Nitro' this past week was embarrassing and the man who is
a legend in the business, has now become a parody of himself. I
find it sad to watch as I have great respect for him, but I can't
condone how he constantly refuses to pass the torch and give the
rub to the future legends of this sport.'' Tell us how you really
feel Chris.
</P>
<P>
   ECW stars Tommy Dreamer and New Jack will guest star in an
episode of the CBS drama ``Early Edition'' in May. In other ECW
news, former tag team champs, The Pitbulls, could be returning.
</P>
<P>
   WWF has lost Billy Gunn to a shoulder injury for up to six
months. He had surgery on the torn rotator cuff last week.
</P>
<P>
   The release date for the WCW movie, ``Ready to Rumble,'' has
been moved up from April 14 to April 7.
</P>
<P>
   Expect to see suspended wrestler Scott Steiner back on WCW
telecasts beginning in April. Also Goldberg is expected to return
from his arm injury before the mid-April pay-per-view.
</P>
<P>
   Speaking of WCW pay-per-views, wrestling expert Dave Meltzer
said the buy rate for February's ``Superbrawl'' is around a .15.
That is the lowest buy rate ever for one of the big two wrestling
companies. He also said it is lower than most ECW buyrates.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
