<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-BONE16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Stars make pulp thriller watchable
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Like ``Double Jeopardy,'' this serial killer drama is, at its
core, pure pulp filmmaking. It delivers plenty of sucker punches.
But thanks to the film's two talented stars _ Denzel Washington as
a brainy quadriplegic detective and Angelina Jolie as his equally
brainy forensics cop _ this thriller's got enough electricity to
make it watchable.
</P>
<P>
   The stars ignite a potent sexual chemistry that gives the film
added weight and helps mask the weakest point plots. (Priced for
rental on VHS; $26.98 DVD, including feature commentary from
director Phillip Noyce.)
</P>
<P>
   `The Bone Collector'
</P>
<P>
   Rated R / Our critic's grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   _Bob Longino
</P>
<P>
   OTHER RELEASES:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Guinevere'' (R) _ A well-bred, well-off college grad (Sarah
Polley) moves in with a 50-ish raffishly scruffy bohemian
photographer (Stephen Rea) who's made something of a career out of
introducing much younger women _ his ``Guineveres'' _ to the joys
of sex, Sartre, jazz, art, etc. But what sounds like grist for a
grim feminist diatribe against our culture's wink-wink approval of
May/December liaisons is actually a sweet, rueful, somewhat
sorrowing love letter. The writing and direction are sharp as a
tack and the acting is gorgeous. Grade: A-
</P>
<P>
   _Eleanor Ringel Gillespie
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Outside Providence'' (R) _ This movie may be written by the
``There's Something About Mary'' gang, but it's bittersweet funny,
not raucous comedy. It's a coming-of-age tale of a '70s Rhode
Island teen (Shawn Hatosy) that captures the shaggy, druggy
``what-next'' feeling that followed in the uncertain years after
the Summer of Love had come and gone. Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   Bob Longino, Eleanor Ringel Gillspie and Steve Murray write for
the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
