   &UR; MONTENEGRO WARNS THAT MILOSEVIC IS UP TO HIS OLD TRICKS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PODGORICA _ Montenegro's leaders have issued a stark warning to
the West that their embattled republic is being destabilized by
Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic as a pretext for a full-scale
invasion by the Yugoslav army. Both the president and the prime
minister warned of the very real dangers of another Balkan
conflagration, perhaps as early as this spring. &QL;
</P>
