   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RETURNING-JEWS (Undated) _ Young people, reared in households
where religion was almost invisible, are turning in great numbers
to traditional forms of Judaism. They are called ``the returning.''
To many of their bewildered and hurt parents, however, they aren't
``returning'' to anything at all. By Marcella Bombardieri. 1600
words. PHOTO
</P>
