</P>
<P>
   YALE-STARTUPS (New Haven, Conn.) _ New Haven, long known for its
declining economy, is getting a shot in the arm with the blossoming
of a biotechnology industry fed by its close ties to Yale
University. By Ronald Rosenberg. 1870 words.
</P>
<P>
   ONJOBS-COLUMN (Undated) -- Despite economic good times, jobs
still elude some. By Diane E. Lewis. 1,500 words.
</P>
