   ONBUSINESS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Critics says Boston Bank of
Commerce has become an arbitrage operation, raising deposits and
investing the money in the bond market. Supporters call it a pillar
of community banking. By Steven Syre and Charles Stein.
</P>
