   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HIGH-TECH-VISAS (Washington) _ A bipartisan coalition of House
members on Wednesday introduced legislation that would boost the
ceiling on visas for foreigners with high-tech skills to 200,000
over the next three years. This year, the lid stands at 150,000. It
would be the second lifting of the cap on so-called H1-B workers in
two years and is similar to legislation moving through the Senate.
By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
