<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-15 14:18 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7643 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r k BC-MORSE-COLUMN-HNS &LR;      03-15 0810
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MORSE-COLUMN-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     THE NRA'S NOT-SO-SHARP SHOOTER 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     Commentary  
 &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By ROB MORSE  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ The National Rifle Association doesn't shoot
people, it shoots itself in the foot.
</P>
<P>
   What in blazing six-guns was the NRA's Wayne LaPierre thinking
when he said that President Clinton ``needs a certain level of
violence in this country.''
</P>
<P>
   What Clinton needs is a certain level of the NRA talking about
violence. When it gets down to LaPierre's level it embarrasses even
Republicans and responsible gun owners.
</P>
<P>
   The NRA has handed the Democrats a winning position on an issue.
You can be sure that George W. Bush knows that LaPierre is
Clinton's concealed weapon. If conservatives know what's good for
them, they'll put a gum-lock on LaPierre's mouth.
</P>
<P>
   In other gun issues: Salon magazine has an article by Jonathan
Rauch advocating the ultimate deterrent to gay-bashing: In states
where carrying concealed weapons is legal, gays should carry guns.
</P>
<P>
   Rauch calls his proposal ``Pink Pistols,'' but I don't know
about that. Is that a pink pistol in your pocket, or are you just
happy to see me?
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Times was bought by the Tribune Co. of Chicago,
and suddenly Angelenos are moaning about the ``colonization'' of
Los Angeles by outside corporations. This comes after years of Los
Angeles colonizing the world via television, records, movies and
Madonna.
</P>
<P>
   It's all a lot of hooey. When Disney bought ABC, did anyone in
New York complain about the colonization of Gotham by Anaheim?
</P>
<P>
   Cities aren't colonizing cities. Corporations are merging,
getting fewer and bigger, and it just happens that some cities lose
out. It's likely that everybody loses out.
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   Well, Hugh McColl hasn't been losing out. First, the chief
executive of Bank of America took the bank's headquarters from San
Francisco to Charlotte, N.C. Now he's reportedly been given $50
million in bonuses despite the bank's poor performance.
</P>
<P>
   So that's where all those charges Bank of America lays on us
have been going. So that's why the bank pays such puny interest.
</P>
<P>
   Talk about colonized. I feel McCollonized.
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   The census form arrived, and it was so official-looking I almost
threw it out, thinking Ed McMahon had finally done it, printing
``Your response is required by law'' on the envelope.
</P>
<P>
   People keep violating the law. In the census 10 years ago,
834,000 Californians, and 21,000 San Franciscans, weren't counted.
</P>
<P>
   Don't ask me who counted these folks who weren't counted, but
maybe that outfit should be hired to replace the current U.S.
Census Bureau _ which is so incompetent it misaddressed 115 million
census forms.
</P>
<P>
   Kenneth Prewitt, director of the Census Bureau, called the
mistake ``cosmetic.''
</P>
<P>
   Which brings up my main objection to the census form. It's one
more thing that makes me and millions of other Americans feel bad
about the color of our skin.
</P>
<P>
   White men can't jump. White men can't dance. Now we have one
more: White men can't check multiple boxes.
</P>
<P>
   The census form allows you to check one or more boxes, such as
white, African-American, American Indian, Chinese, Filipino and a
few others, with room to fill in a race of your choice, and a
separate category for Spanish/Hispanic/Latino.
</P>
<P>
   If you check ``white'' and ``Chinese,'' though, you'll be
counted as Chinese. This is like the old days of the South when any
bit of black blood made you black.
</P>
<P>
   There's something insulting about having to check ``white.''
Sure, we get our share of privileges, like not being pulled over
and shot by cops as often as people of other colors. But after all
these years of discovering our Irish, Italian or Polish heritage,
the U.S. government tells us we're just white.
</P>
<P>
   And some of us are kind of mottled.
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   The dog daze continues. A Virginia animal lovers group has just
donated another $50,000 to the reward fund to find and convict the
miscreant who threw Leo the bichon frise into San Jose traffic.
</P>
<P>
   That brings the total reward to $100,000, and a lot of us are
probably thinking about taking Fido for a one-way ride.
</P>
<P>
   Naw, we wouldn't do that. But where is people's sense of
proportion? What about all those dead skunks on the highways, huh?
Where's the reward for whoever's tossing them into traffic?
</P>
<P>
   And what about a reward for the capture of those guys driving
sleds in the Iditarod race in Alaska?
</P>
<P>
   There's a lesson here. If you're a vicious murderer on death
row, and you want to create sympathy for a stay of execution,
forget about finding Christ or discovering your Native American
roots.
</P>
<P>
   Discover your roots as a bichon frise.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rob Morse is a columnist for the San Francisco Examiner, P.O.
Box 7260, San Francisco, CA 94120.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
