<P>
   CoxNet's second seasonal page of 2000, our annual Oscars ballot,
is now available for download from the New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
<P>
   The full-page treatment features a handy cut-out ballot that
readers can use to check off winners when viewing this year's
Academy Awards telecast on March 26. The page also features color
photos of all the nominees from the major film categories and a
downpage story that directs readers to videos now available that
spotlight the acting skills of this year's crop of nominees.
</P>
<P>
   The page is embargoed until Sunday, March 26, but it is
available for downloading now.
</P>
<P>
   It is perfect for ad sales as well. Ad departments can print the
page out and show it to an advertiser, whose strip ad can easily
replace the downpage story.
</P>
