<P>
   UNDATED _ People don't go to Ireland for the food. But they
would, if they knew more about it. Ireland, where lamb stew and
Guinness stout come to mind. Where salmon reign in the cold,
fast-flowing rivers and the icy Atlantic beyond. Salmon that end up
poached or delicately smoked. Where cream _ whipped alongside your
wedge of chocolate cake or gently piled atop your Irish coffee _ is
tinted slightly yellow, butterlike. Where rainfall averages up to
100 inches a year and the term Emerald Isle'' is no misnomer _ it's
an understatement. The cows are fat and their cream is rich. Even
oatmeal tastes better here. By CAROL NUCKOLS. Story has moved in
