   RECIPES-BUNDY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Readers spill the beans about desserts. By BEVERLY
BUNDY. Story has moved in ``d'' food and dining category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ OK. Super Tuesday and Super Tuesday II are history.
The remaining presidential primaries are like the final games of
the baseball season, those meaningless contests that must be played
even though playoff slots have been divvied up and fans are
counting the days until the World Series begins. The World Series
of politics takes place this year on Nov. 7, when citizens of the
planet's lone remaining superpower elect a new president. What do
you suppose we'll talk about 'til then? By BILL THOMPSON. Story has
moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
