<P>
   GORE-PENNSYLVANIA (Philadelphia) _ Pennsylvania voters have
nearly always picked the winning presidential candidate for the
last four decades, and with that in mind, Vice President Al Gore
wasted no time heading there to stake his claim to the key
battleground. In Philadelphia, he courted union workers, raised
money, picked up the endorsement of Mayor John Street and visited a
vocational school. By BENNETT ROTH. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-GUNS (Austin, Texas) _ Under fire from Democrats as weak on
gun control, Texas Gov. George W. Bush says he could support a law
requiring every new firearm to include technology that would allow
the weapons to be fired only when matched to the owner's
fingerprints. By R.G. RATCLIFFE. (Already filed.)
