INTEL-AWARDS-SCHOOL-2 -- Paul D. Schreiber High School achieved a
stunning victory in the nationwide Intel Science Talent Search this
year, producing the first-place winner and two other finalists.
Perhaps the main reason that students here excell in such a contest
is that 15 years ago the school started a program to teach students
how to perform sophisticated research. Phyllis Serfaty, a biology
teacher who heads the program, said the work created a rigorous
schedule for teachers as well as the 90 students involved. (Vic
DeLucia/The New York Times)
